> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Korean Style
> Gochujang Beef Fried Rice in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Rice and Beans ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it comes to the boil, trim the @green beans{150%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{5-6%minutes}. You'll finish cooking it in
step 3 with the green beans.

== Beef ==

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%grams} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a
#spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the mince fries, crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using
a #rolling pin{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Combining Rice and Beans ==

Once the rice has cooked for ~{5-6%minutes}, add the green beans to same pan and cook
for ~{5-6%minutes} more.

Once both the rice and beans are cooked, drain in a #sieve{}.

Pop the sieve on top of the pan and allow to steam until ready to use.

== Sauce and Finishing ==

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

> The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir through the garlic and @gochujang paste{80%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder). Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @honey{15%grams}, @soy sauce{25%milliliters} and @water{50%milliliters}
for the sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the
@butter{20%grams} until melted.

== Assembling the Dish ==

Add the cooked rice and green beans to the beef frying pan.

Mix together well so the rice is nicely coated in the sauce.

Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

Share the gochujang beef fried rice between your serving bowls.

Scatter over the peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!